\begin_layout Subsection
The Value of Backups
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As a general rule, LyX is rock-solid and works like a Swiss watch.
 However, the very nature of LaTeX files means that sometimes something
 can get messed up and render your document un-compilable (this can happen
 with MS Word too, when your document gets corrupted).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To avoid any such surprises, especially just before the deadline, it is
 strongly recommended to use a general purpose file backup programme such
 as 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "Dropbox"
target "https://www.dropbox.com/"

\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "SpiderOak"
target "https://spideroak.com/"

\end_inset

.
 Both are free to use, cross-platform and 
\emph on
very
\emph default
 easy to set up.
 They are also extremely easy to use in your day-to-day computer work.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The effort is minimal, and the benefits could be highly rewarding (as in:
 `you managed to submit the thesis in time').
 Thus, when something strange happens and you can no longer compile your
 document and cannot find the root cause, you can simply (and easily) revert
 to an older version of your document using one of these tools.
\end_layout

